1784 Rec 'd a better account of Mr. Vesey . dreſs 'd for ye . day -- Lady Wake came

days in it . but he finds
went to our Rooms A complete Thaw today
were gone to bed -- 23 d . A letter from my friend Mrs. Vesey 24 th . Febry . 1784
Tuesday . At ½ past 12 Miſs C— 's
Wednesday 25 th : had Mrs. Iremonger . Miſs Clarkes -- Miſs Glover -- Lady Stormont they each staid
went to bed -- ye . Miſs C— call 'd when I was out in ye . Morning Friday
went to bed abt . 12 o'Clock . Recd . a good account of Miſs A M Clarke Saturday
s between our Lady F Harpur & Lady Warwick a few days ago
told me Genl : Clarke was yesterday
were Retired to their Rooms -- Sunday
had been indisposed two or three days ago
yesterday a little past 11 Mr. Glover & I came
went immediately to my Room Monday
is only come to Town for a few day
is still confined wth . a fall she had some months
½ past 11 -- Miſs Hamilton calld when I was out in ye- Morning Wednesday
March 1784 dreſs 'd for ye . day when I got up
March 1784 I was not quite well therefore excused
March 1784 I was not quite well & got up
had made visits & enquiries for me at other places 6 th . March 1784
conversed together till 4 o'Clock -- Mrs. D : her Neice . & Mrs. Walkinshaw a child of 12 years
March . Lady C Finch ye . Stay Maker came
went to Mr. Vesey Party tomorrow
send me a Nosegay for Wednesday
hear Carlton House was not clear 'd before 9 in ye . Morning . Thursday March 11
came out of ye . Country to us Yesterday
paid her for all the things I had on Wednesday
1614 There is a revolting aſsurance & bluntness in quque Quaker 's
6 years of his with his civilities -- he is ye . only person I ever was obliged
had told their Servts . his Wife was yesterday
went to our Rooms Sunday 14 March 1784
went to bed & c & c . Sunday March 14
84 years of age , & the tears were trickling down
now -- ( but she will not endulge
told me there was to be Ball at Carleton House ye . 1 st . of April
was going in a fortnight for 6 weeks
wrote great part of it when he was but 15 years
March 1784 had my breakfast & dreſs 'd for ye . day . Mrs. Glover wd . not come
got to my Room & c & c Wednesday
March -- Saw Miſs Clarkes before she went out
said it was in ye . true Italian Taste & that even now
went to bed at ½ past 11 Thursday
sat a good while with me . she was but indifferarent wth . her Head ache . She had been since I saw
